The exchange rates are 1 pound = 1.64 USD and 1 euro = 1.32 USD. We need to determine how many more euros than pounds she will have after rounding to the nearest whole number. 1. **Calculate the amount to withdraw in pounds and euros:** - Half of 300 USD is 150 USD. - Convert 150 USD to pounds: \[ \frac{150}{1.64} \approx 91.46 \text{ pounds} \] - Convert 150 USD to euros: \[ \frac{150}{1.32} \approx 113.64 \text{ euros} \] 2. **Determine the difference between the number of euros and pounds:** - Subtract the number of pounds from the number of euros: \[ 113.64 - 91.46 = 22.18 \] - Round the result to the nearest whole number: \[ 22.18 \approx 22 \] Thus, Kathy will have \(\boxed{22}\) more euros than pounds.
